div.p:
Take the Juice of the inner rind of the Elder, give thereof two
ounces to the Patient to drink in a Glaſs of Cows Milk an hour before Meals;
this will make you void much Flegm, and Purges gently.

Take freſh Horſe-dung, and fry it with freſh Greaſe;
then preſs out the Juice, through a Cloth, with which you ſhall anoint the
Part afflicted, laying a Paper thereon.

Take half an ounce of Bean-flowers, Lime, and Eggs an ounce;
white Salt one pound, Water of Confound, Alcobol of Wine eleven ounces;
diſtill them and uſe it.

Some keep them in Aſhes, or Oat-ſtraw, and bury their
Veſſel in the ſaid ſtraw, and ſo they keep two years if you will;
others uſe Millet inſtead of Sand.

div.head:
To caſt Medals or carved Figures in traſparent Colours;
to Embelliſh Glaſſes, Windows, or Shaſhes as if they were of Ruby,
Amber, or Coral.
